independence. As the first of the African states to win independence I think we have shown the world. Despite some economic hiccups which come with a new democratic government, I think we have gained a lot from our freedom from those two decades of a single party rule.

I made comparison remarks like you. However the good side of your argument is evidenced by your rejoinder showing your love for the country. I do appreciate the wishes. Best wishes also to you and yours Motsamai. Again, thank you so much.

I am proud to be a Basotho knowing that my country has educated me till 7th grade + 2 credit, remember every citizen of this country pays 3,516 MTN shares as on September 2011, I have spent 14 years, 22 months, 36 days in the army, and I retire with emotional pension worth more than than thessssh Just a vivid look to 24 years since independence, can not be completed within 3,516 words as basutuls claimed, than my own surname will record in history , the Basutuls loves -> National renaissance

Patriot,

How do you suspect that 3566 shares did for me,as a father of six to educate all of them? Without my dedicated efforts,a low,hard work ethics,others will laugh at my expense.Are you out of your mind,please read history and you will know that there is no relation between soldiers and shares.
